Looking at the balance sheet, I can see there's a line item labeled "Taxes Payable". This represents taxes that have been accrued but not yet paid to the relevant tax authorities.

From the balance sheet data:
- The initial value for "Taxes Payable" as of 2023-12-31 is 0.00
- The end value for "Taxes Payable" as of 2024-01-29 is 299588.25

These values represent the tax liability that has been recognized on the books but not yet paid.
